@startuml
title Stable Tool Surface Key Persistence

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Monospaced

start
:Persisted workspace layout entry is loaded;

if (Legacy ToolSurfaceKind / PersistedToolSurfaceKindV2?) then (yes)
  :Use versioned compatibility adapter;
  :Produce stable surface key candidate;
else (already stable key)
  :Use persisted stable surface key;
endif

:Look up stable key in active ToolSurfaceRegistry;

if (Stable key known?) then (no)
  :Emit diagnostic artifact;
  :Fail closed with no provider-local routes;
  :Do not silently map to another tool;
  stop
else (yes)
  if (Removed or incompatible?) then (yes)
    :Reject activation or preserve current workspace;
    :Emit compatibility diagnostic;
    :Registry activation alone must not rewrite WorkspaceState;
    stop
  else (known and compatible)
    :Mount ToolSurfaceInstanceId;
    :Resolve provider;
    :Build surface frame;
  endif
endif

:Registry activation alone leaves WorkspaceState unchanged;

if (Explicit workspace layout apply requested?) then (yes)
  :Validate layout definition against registry;
  :Apply workspace mutation through governed shell command;
else (no)
  :Keep existing WorkspaceState unchanged;
endif

stop

note right
  Stable keys replace ever-growing persisted
  enum variants for registry-owned surfaces.
  Compatibility adapters are allowed
  during migration.
  Unknown keys must never silently become
  the wrong tool.
  Explicit workspace layout apply is
  required for layout mutation.
end note

@enduml
